			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Hello my fellow Dark brothers, i have a story for you about this wonderful spell AOD. In my 19th season as a necro, i had already purchased all of my lvl 20 spells. I was merely hunting gargoyles in oot for the loot and the exp. Once i leveled, i quickly scribed all my spells, and decided to try AOD out since i was oom anyway. (Careful Boyz) this spell will kill u!  I cast AOD on myself a very nice upgrade to dark pact, and notcied that my hp's were being lost at a very &quot;fast&quot; rate. Though the mana transfer is almost if not equal to breeze, YOU HAVE TO BE CAREFUL with this spell untill about lvl 23. Anyway i countinued to read the veteran necro's tips on how to cope with this spell, and if done properly, u can always keep it on with almost no hp's lost. Cast Aod, then engul drk, leach, any dots, and siphon life. Any hp's that u lose or lost will be giving back to u from the leach and the siphon life.<BR>
And the leach countinues to work even after the mob is dead. :) One last story, I was hunting gargoyles in oot again at lvl 23, there was a DE necro, and a DE wizard camping the specs there. They didnt mind at all that i was taking the little mobs at all. :) Lol any, i was doing my thing, slaying the gargs, getting eyes every now and then. The other 2 countinued to pull specs and do their thing. Here is the FUNNY part! Midway through my battles, I decied to cast AOD to med up. I was already minus 1 bulb of health, I cast AOD, pulled my mob and started fighting. What I didnt know was that the other 2 had pulled a spec and the spec was getting the best of them. Know this duo was really and efficiently killing these specs with the exception of this one. Anyway Im dancing with the gargoyle and all of a sudden i get slashed for 191 pts of damage!! My pet immediately and faithfully attacked the spec (lvl 20 pet :() Un beknownst to me, the DE necro had cast Feign Death and the PISSED off spec turned to the next target. ME. With my pets health damn near 0 I cast gate. And guess where my bind point was.....YEP... freeport docks! Anyway as soon as the loading screen went away, i noticed that i had 1 bulb of life left and AOD was still on! The only other person on the dock was some new person that look frightned that he had never seen a DE before... Anyway i sat there for about 5secs, and rather than go through the hassle of try to even get a heal, was dead from my own spell AOD within 1min. Luckily for me i died AT my bind point and the nec that casted the feign death that caused me to evac was nice enough to research  my lvl 24 pet buff intensify death for me.....  :)
				</font>
